# frontend-architecture

The frontend architecture consists of the following key components:

## Interactive UI Components

Located in `HomeLab/modules/HomeLab.UI`:

1. Deployment Form Component (Importance: 85)
- Interactive GUI form for Azure infrastructure deployment
- Dynamic repository listing integration with GitHub API
- Real-time input validation and subscription info pre-population
- Custom domain configuration interface

2. Custom Domain Manager (Importance: 75) 
- Domain configuration workflow UI
- SSL certificate management interface
- DNS record configuration panels

3. Cost Dashboard (Importance: 80)
- Resource cost visualization
- Budget tracking interface
- Cost optimization recommendations display

## State Management

Located in `HomeLab/modules/HomeLab.UI/DeploymentModule`:

1. Deployment State Handler (Importance: 90)
- Manages deployment progress state
- Handles environment configuration persistence
- Tracks VPN and gateway connection states

2. Configuration State (Importance: 85)
- Environment type selection state
- Location and project settings
- Azure subscription details
- Custom domain configurations

## UI Patterns

1. Form Generation System (Importance: 75)
- Dynamic form generation based on deployment type
- Contextual validation rules
- Progressive disclosure of form fields

2. Status Indicators (Importance: 70)
- Deployment progress visualization
- Resource health status display
- Connection state indicators

